Guide to installing and configuring an NTP server on Ubuntu server v20.04.3

Legend: $ = Command to run on command line
	# = Comments

Installation
1. Update/upgrade repository
	$ sudo apt-get update
	$ sudo apt-get upgrade
2. Install NTP Server with apt
	$ sudo apt-get install ntp
3. Verify installation
	$ sntp --version

Configuraton
1. Switch to an NTP server pool according to your destination at https://support.ntp.org/bin/view/Servers/NTPPoolServers
	# delete the pool list and replace it with the pool list from the website that best match your location
	$ sudo vim /etc/ntp.conf
2. Restart NTP Server
	$ sudo service ntp restart
3. Verify that the NTP Server is running
	$ sudo service ntp status
4. Configure Firewall so that clients can access NTP Server
	# Configure your UFW firewall to accept connections at UDP Port 123
	$ sudo ufw allow from any to any port 123 proto udp	
